    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>The metric space axioms are easy to verify computationally. The deep results (Heine-Borel, completeness of R, Banach fixed point) are theorems that our code illustrates but cannot prove. The contraction mapping iteration is the constructive content of the Banach theorem: it gives you the fixed point and a convergence rate.</p>

